sentences: Dieter Ulrich (12 October 1958 in Zurich) is a Swiss jazz and free improvisation musician (percussion, flugelhorn) and art historian.
Ulrich had piano lessons from Irma Schaichet from 1965 to 1980.
He learned also playing percussion by self study from 1972.
In 1988, he played with his own quintet in the Jazz Festival Zurich.
